did.abstract: This collection consists of buttons (including election buttons, dues buttons, etc.), lapel pins, keychains, watches, textiles, and other small collectible items related to the International Brotherhood of Teamsters. Items date from the early 1910's to the present day, with the bulk of the material dating between 1940 and 1990.
did.physloc: Materials are stored off-site, and will require additional retrieval time. Please contact the Special Collections Research Center for more information.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection consists of buttons (including election buttons, dues buttons, etc.), lapel pins, keychains, watches, textiles, and other small collectible items related to the International Brotherhood of Teamsters. Items date from the early 1910's to the present day, with the bulk of the material dating between 1940 and 1990.

This collection consists of six significant donations from William "Bill" Moore, Norma Bartus, Earl Randall, Regina Gormley, Cheryl Johnson and Leo Deaner in addition to donations from other Teamster affiliated persons and some material acquired through purchase. Items were collected while the donors were active in the International Brotherhood of Teamsters and represent a mix of contemporary items and historic memorabilia, some of which were acquired from immediate family members of the donors.

Unique items of interest include a pair of gavels, a copper sheet etched with a letter of praise for the Teamsterettes of Topeka, Kansas, and several pins and buttons from midwestern local unions donated by Bill Moore, an organizer for IBT local union #696 for over thirty years. Also of interest are IBT conference attendee medals worn by members of the Gormley family, and a series of buttons documenting IBT activism during the late 20th century donated by Bartus.

acqinfo.p: Gift of William (Bill) Moore, 13 Jan 2011, Accession 2011.047; Gift of Norma Bartus, 22 Jun 2011, Accession 2011.053 ; Gift of Regina Gormley; Gift of Earl Randall, Gift of Cheryl Johnson, Gift of Leo Deaner; Miscellaneous Purchases

accessrestrict.head: Restrictions on Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into 7 series: Gift of Bill Moore, Gift of Norma Bartis, Gift of Earl Randall, Gift of Regina Gormley, Miscellaneous Acquistions, Gift of Cheryl Johnson and Gift of Leo Deaner.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Please cite unpublished materials in the following way:
Please provide the title and date of item, catalog number (if applicable it will be found written on the folder), name of the collection, name of the repository, and location of the repository.

Example: James Oglethorpe to the Trustees, 13 January 1876, RG0001 Series 1, Box 4, Folder 3. Records of the Board of Trustees, Special Collections Research Center, Gelman Library, The George Washington University, Washington, D.C.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of political and dues buttons, lapel pins, miscellaneous small memorabilia items such as keychains, and textiles, including an IBT vest, flag, and 2013 Women's Conference shirt and tote bag. Some of these items were acquired through small donations, while others were purchased.
